{"questionId":"9073127","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The force acting between two point charges is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></em> when the separation of the charges is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math></em>. What is the force between the charges when the separation is increased to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></math>?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073127","referenceCode":"19N.1.HL.TZ0.31","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The force acting between two point charges is F when the separation of the charges is x. What is the force between the charges when the separation is increased to 3x? A. F3 B. F3x2","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"31","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.1 – Electric fields","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}